race.comment: DONITA BALE (2) is a handy type who was well below best latest at Geelong, finishing eighth (26.32) in a Grade 4/5. Normally safely away but always well back and facing a task from wide out last time. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. ZIPPING SINGH (3) is worth forgiving for his last effort when fourth (30.50) at this track over 525m. Leading chance. BELFAST SPOT (6) missed the frame latest but had been racing well prior to that including a Grade 5 win two back (29.94) at Sandown. Expected to do much better this time. HERO BLUES (8) is in the mix despite missing out at this track last time.
